HEADWORD: Hagiology
<hw>Ha`gi*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(-j⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"a`gios</grk> sacred + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The history or
description of the sacred writings or of sacred persons; a narrative of
the lives of the saints; a catalogue of saints.</def> <rj><au>J. H.
Newman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

